HEADWORD: Seraskier
<hw>Se*ras"kier</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Turk., fr. Per.
<ets>ser</ets> head, chief + Ar. <ets>'asker</ets> an army.]</ety>
<def>A general or commander of land forces in the Turkish empire;
especially, the commander-in-chief of minister of war.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

